<br>
Sure I can control my agro, but do you really want me rooting every mob incoming so I can safely slow without the cleric dumping 3x more mana keeping me alive than the tank?  I think not.<br>
<br>
When I do use root in pickup groups, there is always some melee that starts complaining because they can't just run up to the mob and hit autoattack, then minimize EQ and do whatever it is that they do for the 45 seconds until the mob drops.<br>
<br>
Point.. it's just as much the tanks responsibility to hold agro as it is the rest of the group to control their own agro.  Do I change my strategy depending on the tank? Yes.  I've had pally tanks that were by far worse than a mediocre warrior at agro.  I've had sk tanks that might as well been, as I saw put today, ranjurs.<br>
<br>
/cheer <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425876" target="top"><br>
