<br>
What you need is a better haste item and/or a bigger weapon.<br>
<br>
Any other solution to agro maintenance just doesn't allow the ego room to breath and should be shunned.<br>
<br>
mucho haste + big weapon = tons of agro.<br>
<br>
If you cannot afford better haste &amp; a big weapon? Dont bitch about it, just accept that your gear is crap and find a solution to the problem.<br>
<br>
What about the agro is all about playskill argument?<br>
<br>
Skill in agro management is about controlling X number of mobs and accomplishing the CC with the minimal of mana expenditure and within CC/Heal cast time constraints, in order to maintain the highest killspeed over time.<br>
<br>
If you rely on spells to establish or keep agro on the main mob then you cannot possibly ACC on the adds. Furthermore you are delivering less dps. Your are not pulling your weight.<br>
<br>
The main tank should at all times know what mob is hitting who and be able to decide instantly which mobs they need to agro and where to place them.<br>
<br>
If you are struggling to keep agro by chain casting, you can at best control 1 mob and any attempt to ACC will probably fail or take too long to accomplish anything<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You, sir, obviously don't play the same game I do. Spells alone I can keep aggro on up to 3, 4 mobs at once in LDoN &quot;rain&quot; groups. Almost every pull is intentionally a double pull where I double tank. WITH SPELLS. Rarely do I lose aggro, and if I do it's usually just a bounce right back to me in under a second. Weapon, in those cases, means absolutely jack and shit.<br>
<br>
And of course let's not forget the advantages of not swinging your weapon at all while tanking mobs that hit big + fast, or off-tanking mobs you don't want to hit summon mode on boss encounters... or do you not know what those advantages are? <p><CENTER><HR width="75%"><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220954"><B>Duke Vendric Ravenkrest, Tier`Dal Dread Lord of Hate</B></A><BR><TABLE border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="75%"><TR><TD><I>"I walk the Earth, another day. The wicked one, that comes this way. Savior to my own, devil to some. Mankind falls, something wicked comes."</I></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daramineq>DaraminEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 220<br> <font color=#330000>(11/23/03 7:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1154.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tank Rant!!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Well you said there is no reason to go through the 'routine' you go through.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Oh, you want to know? Happy to tell you, but before I do, keep in mind it doesn't generate agro like an SK or PAL can do, but it's the best that I can come up with.<br>
<br>
1) prefer to pull myself, since that's a bit of extra agro -- &quot;first contact&quot; with the mob seems to be worth about 100-200 pts of agro. Irrelevant in the long run, so I don't make a big deal about it.<br>
<br>
2) Try to put one or two arrows on it on the way into camp, LDoN this is hard sometimes.<br>
<br>
3) Once the mob is in camp, turn attack on, big whoop. Generally it gets on me immediately at that point, unless someone pulled with a debuff. If they pulled with a debuff, immediately taunt. My taunt key also has disarm in it.<br>
<br>
4) If the mob isn't debuffed, I go through a routine that varies depending on the people there and what routine they use, it comes down to:<br>
<br>
If) Shaman Maloing on inc, slowing<br>
    Chanter tashing<br>
<br>
Then) If the chanter is tashing quickly, I wait for slow *and* tash to be in before I taunt. Malo doesn't get the shammy agro, so I ignore it. If they're doing malosinia/etc on inc I generally ask them to stop. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If) Chanter tashing and slowing both<br>
<br>
Then) If they do tash then slow, I can taunt on both. If they slow then tash (yes, some do), then I have to hope I've generated enough agro to outdo the slow, then taunt after the tash. If I haven't, then I taunt on the slow, and most chanters are smart enough not to tash a mob that is hitting them. The ones that really piss me off are the ones that slow, see that I got agro back and 1s later tash. Guess what, taunt hasn't refreshed yet!<br>
<br>
Chanter slow is about 450 pts of agro, tash is a little less, Shaman slow is about like chanter tash. Generally one stun proc from my GBoS will negate a slow or a tash, but not both. An EB proc from my BoC (rare to have one in the first 10s since I offhand it) will negate both sometimes, just depends on how many times I've whiffed. Recently I have a Call of Sky proc from an item I got in VT, which adds another stun chance to my repertoire. It generates just as much agro as any other stun from what I can tell.<br>
<br>
If at some point I've failed a taunt check and the mob is beating someone in the head still, I shield them. Some folks think there is some agro associated with shielding a player, I don't think there is, but at least I can soak up some of their damage. I'm necessarily in the mob's face at that point for /shield to work, but I would be anyway.<br>
<br>
I generally have time for one more taunt in there before I feel like a total chump. If I miss that one and I haven't procced at all, I let the group know what's going on, and that I'm not AFK. If I've procced at all, by the time I've tried to taunt off the debuffer twice I have agro anyway.<br>
<br>
<br>
That's how I get through the first 10s of the fight. Basically I'm not mashing taunt, I'm waiting for high agro debuffs to land and then taunting once they do. If someone is down to 40% health and I think they're about to die, I AE taunt, and tell the group that they need to not suck for the next 15 minutes.<br>
<br>
Generally, the group adjusts to my levels of agro and I don't have to do anything extreme after that. So if warrior was the only class I played, I'd be feeling like there's nothing horribly broken with the class, I do just fine. However, I also have a 65 necromancer, 62 cleric, and 56 chanter, so I see the world from their point of view too.<br>
<br>
When I'm on the necro, and a warrior is in the group, I don't bother trying to Thule the mob. It won't live long enough to run for full if I wait until I won't have agro from using it. Horror apparently is less agro, I gotta do a couple more LDoN so he has that one. I can usually FP pretty quick, but not on inc exactly. Since Thule and FP are my two fastest dots, nothing else is really worth talking about. I don't lifetap with the dot, since I have the AA that makes my lifetaps crit a lot. Generally I use neurotoxin once or twice more and suck some mana for the group off the mob if it casts. I can't stack Thule and FP at *all* with a warrior tank, it gets me agro every tick. Those are about 150 DPS counting the pet, but not counting burning affliction, so that gives you an idea of the limit past which I can't go with a warrior in group.<br>
<br>
When I'm on the cleric, I SR a lot more with a warrior in group. If a PAL/SK is tanking, I can rest assured that agro is going to be locked on them, so I can cast the 10s CH without fear. If a warrior is tanking I generally drop an elixir on them right away, to provide a bit of buffer, then see how things go. I don't have a lot of AA on the cleric, but Divine Arbitration and Celestial Regeneration are on my list to get. It's not at all uncommon for me to need a med break after a bad pull where I had to SR a lot because the warrior couldn't hold agro.<br>
<br>
Chanter is just a game of figuring out how long I have to wait before I can tash safely. 10-15s seems to be the rule, if the person has completely ass weapons I have on at least one occasion asked for a short break so I could go to the bazaar and buy the poor guy a GSoT (200pp, omg, break the bank). He was very happy, he had no idea it was any good.<br>
